# Project context
This is a fork project from a template provided by Vercel : chat SDK/

Chat SDK is a free, open-source template built with Next.js and the AI SDK that helps you quickly build powerful chatbot applications.

# Technical Stack
- NextJS, 
- next-intl, 
- Vercel AI SDK, 
- Support multiple LLM
- Lucid, 
- Shadcn, 
- TailwindCSS, 
- Lucide-react, 
- HTML, 
- CSS. 

Do not use any other libraries or frameworks unless it's explicitly required. 
Ask me an approval before using any other library or framework.

Deployed on Vercel or as a docker container.

# Git Usage
Commit messages prefix should be:
- [FEAT] for new features
- [FIX] for bug fixes
- [DOC] for documentation
- [REFACTOR] for code refactoring
- [STYLE] for code style changes
- [PERF] for performance improvements
- [TEST] for adding or modifying tests
- [CHORE] for other changes that don't modify src or test files

Rules : 
- Commit messages should be in English.
- Commit messages should be clear and concise.
- Use lowercase for commit messages.
- Keep commit messages short and to the point.
- Include description for non-trivial changes.

# Documentation

- Use Markdown to write documentation.
- Maintain the README.md file up to date with the latest information.
- Add comments to all components, functions, hooks, types, utils, etc.
- Add comments for complex logic.

# Dependencies
- Use pnpm as the package manager.



